In the Matter of PRAIRIE GARAGE, Inc.. Debtor. PRAIRIE GARAGE, Inc., v. BOARD OF EDUCATION OF THE CITY OF CHICAGO. No. 5600. Circuit Court of Appeals, Seventh Circuit. Nov. 8, 1935. George S. Pines, of Chicago, Ill., for appellant. Richard S. Folsom, of Chicago, Ill., for appellee.

Before EVANS and SPARKS, Circuit Judges, and LINDLEY, District Judge.

PER CURIAM.

On motion of counsel for appellant,, it is now here ordered, adjudged, and decreed by this court that this appeal be, and the same is hereby, dismissed,, with costs.
